00596 /******************************************************************************/
00597 /*                         Peripheral memory map                              */
00598 /******************************************************************************/
00599 /* Peripheral and SRAM base address in the alias region */
00600 #define PERIPH_BB_BASE        ((u32)0x42000000)
00601 #define SRAM_BB_BASE          ((u32)0x22000000)
00602 
00603 /* Peripheral and SRAM base address in the bit-band region */
00604 #define SRAM_BASE             ((u32)0x20000000)
00605 #define PERIPH_BASE           ((u32)0x40000000)
00606 
00607 /* FSMC registers base address */
00608 #define FSMC_R_BASE           ((u32)0xA0000000)
00609 
00610 /* Peripheral memory map */
00611 #define APB1PERIPH_BASE       PERIPH_BASE
00612 #define APB2PERIPH_BASE       (PERIPH_BASE + 0x10000)
00613 #define AHBPERIPH_BASE        (PERIPH_BASE + 0x20000)
00614 
00615 #define TIM2_BASE             (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x0000)
00616 #define TIM3_BASE             (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x0400)
00617 #define TIM4_BASE             (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x0800)
00618 #define TIM5_BASE             (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x0C00)
00619 #define TIM6_BASE             (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x1000)
00620 #define TIM7_BASE             (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x1400)
00621 #define RTC_BASE              (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x2800)
00622 #define WWDG_BASE             (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x2C00)
00623 #define IWDG_BASE             (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x3000)
00624 #define SPI2_BASE             (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x3800)
00625 #define SPI3_BASE             (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x3C00)
00626 #define USART2_BASE           (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x4400)
00627 #define USART3_BASE           (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x4800)
00628 #define UART4_BASE            (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x4C00)
00629 #define UART5_BASE            (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x5000)
00630 #define I2C1_BASE             (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x5400)
00631 #define I2C2_BASE             (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x5800)
00632 #define CAN_BASE              (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x6400)
00633 #define BKP_BASE              (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x6C00)
00634 #define PWR_BASE              (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x7000)
00635 #define DAC_BASE              (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x7400)
00636 
00637 #define AFIO_BASE             (APB2PERIPH_BASE + 0x0000)
00638 #define EXTI_BASE             (APB2PERIPH_BASE + 0x0400)
00639 #define GPIOA_BASE            (APB2PERIPH_BASE + 0x0800)
00640 #define GPIOB_BASE            (APB2PERIPH_BASE + 0x0C00)
00641 #define GPIOC_BASE            (APB2PERIPH_BASE + 0x1000)
00642 #define GPIOD_BASE            (APB2PERIPH_BASE + 0x1400)
00643 #define GPIOE_BASE            (APB2PERIPH_BASE + 0x1800)
00644 #define GPIOF_BASE            (APB2PERIPH_BASE + 0x1C00)
00645 #define GPIOG_BASE            (APB2PERIPH_BASE + 0x2000)
00646 #define ADC1_BASE             (APB2PERIPH_BASE + 0x2400)
00647 #define ADC2_BASE             (APB2PERIPH_BASE + 0x2800)
00648 #define TIM1_BASE             (APB2PERIPH_BASE + 0x2C00)
00649 #define SPI1_BASE             (APB2PERIPH_BASE + 0x3000)
00650 #define TIM8_BASE             (APB2PERIPH_BASE + 0x3400)
00651 #define USART1_BASE           (APB2PERIPH_BASE + 0x3800)
00652 #define ADC3_BASE             (APB2PERIPH_BASE + 0x3C00)
00653 
00654 #define SDIO_BASE             (PERIPH_BASE + 0x18000)
00655 
00656 #define DMA1_BASE             (AHBPERIPH_BASE + 0x0000)
00657 #define DMA1_Channel1_BASE    (AHBPERIPH_BASE + 0x0008)
00658 #define DMA1_Channel2_BASE    (AHBPERIPH_BASE + 0x001C)
00659 #define DMA1_Channel3_BASE    (AHBPERIPH_BASE + 0x0030)
00660 #define DMA1_Channel4_BASE    (AHBPERIPH_BASE + 0x0044)
00661 #define DMA1_Channel5_BASE    (AHBPERIPH_BASE + 0x0058)
00662 #define DMA1_Channel6_BASE    (AHBPERIPH_BASE + 0x006C)
00663 #define DMA1_Channel7_BASE    (AHBPERIPH_BASE + 0x0080)
00664 #define DMA2_BASE             (AHBPERIPH_BASE + 0x0400)
00665 #define DMA2_Channel1_BASE    (AHBPERIPH_BASE + 0x0408)
00666 #define DMA2_Channel2_BASE    (AHBPERIPH_BASE + 0x041C)
00667 #define DMA2_Channel3_BASE    (AHBPERIPH_BASE + 0x0430)
00668 #define DMA2_Channel4_BASE    (AHBPERIPH_BASE + 0x0444)
00669 #define DMA2_Channel5_BASE    (AHBPERIPH_BASE + 0x0458)
00670 #define RCC_BASE              (AHBPERIPH_BASE + 0x1000)
00671 #define CRC_BASE              (AHBPERIPH_BASE + 0x3000)
00672 
00673 /* Flash registers base address */
00674 #define FLASH_R_BASE          (AHBPERIPH_BASE + 0x2000)
00675 /* Flash Option Bytes base address */
00676 #define OB_BASE               ((u32)0x1FFFF800)
00677 
00678 /* FSMC Bankx registers base address */
00679 #define FSMC_Bank1_R_BASE     (FSMC_R_BASE + 0x0000)
00680 #define FSMC_Bank1E_R_BASE    (FSMC_R_BASE + 0x0104)
00681 #define FSMC_Bank2_R_BASE     (FSMC_R_BASE + 0x0060)
00682 #define FSMC_Bank3_R_BASE     (FSMC_R_BASE + 0x0080)

01187 /*                                                                            */
01188 /******************************************************************************/
01189 
01190 /*******************  Bit definition for CRC_DR register  *********************/
01191 #define  CRC_DR_DR                           ((u32)0xFFFFFFFF) /* Data register bits */
01192 
01193 
01194 /*******************  Bit definition for CRC_IDR register  ********************/
01195 #define  CRC_IDR_IDR                         ((u8)0xFF)        /* General-purpose 8-bit data register bits */
01196 
01197 
01198 /********************  Bit definition for CRC_CR register  ********************/
01199 #define  CRC_CR_RESET                        ((u8)0x01)        /* RESET bit */
01200 
01201 
01202 
01203 /******************************************************************************/
01204 /*                                                                            */
01205 /*                             Power Control                                  */
01206 /*                                                                            */
01207 /******************************************************************************/
01208 
01209 /********************  Bit definition for PWR_CR register  ********************/
01210 #define  PWR_CR_LPDS                         ((u16)0x0001)     /* Low-Power Deepsleep */
01211 #define  PWR_CR_PDDS                         ((u16)0x0002)     /* Power Down Deepsleep */
01212 #define  PWR_CR_CWUF                         ((u16)0x0004)     /* Clear Wakeup Flag */
01213 #define  PWR_CR_CSBF                         ((u16)0x0008)     /* Clear Standby Flag */
01214 #define  PWR_CR_PVDE                         ((u16)0x0010)     /* Power Voltage Detector Enable */
01215 
01216 #define  PWR_CR_PLS                          ((u16)0x00E0)     /* PLS[2:0] bits (PVD Level Selection) */
01217 #define  PWR_CR_PLS_0                        ((u16)0x0020)     /* Bit 0 */
01218 #define  PWR_CR_PLS_1                        ((u16)0x0040)     /* Bit 1 */
01219 #define  PWR_CR_PLS_2                        ((u16)0x0080)     /* Bit 2 */
01220 
01221 /* PVD level configuration */
01222 #define  PWR_CR_PLS_2V2                      ((u16)0x0000)     /* PVD level 2.2V */
01223 #define  PWR_CR_PLS_2V3                      ((u16)0x0020)     /* PVD level 2.3V */
01224 #define  PWR_CR_PLS_2V4                      ((u16)0x0040)     /* PVD level 2.4V */
01225 #define  PWR_CR_PLS_2V5                      ((u16)0x0060)     /* PVD level 2.5V */
01226 #define  PWR_CR_PLS_2V6                      ((u16)0x0080)     /* PVD level 2.6V */
01227 #define  PWR_CR_PLS_2V7                      ((u16)0x00A0)     /* PVD level 2.7V */
01228 #define  PWR_CR_PLS_2V8                      ((u16)0x00C0)     /* PVD level 2.8V */
01229 #define  PWR_CR_PLS_2V9                      ((u16)0x00E0)     /* PVD level 2.9V */
01230 
01231 #define  PWR_CR_DBP                          ((u16)0x0100)     /* Disable Backup Domain write protection */
01232 
01233 
01234 /*******************  Bit definition for PWR_CSR register  ********************/
01235 #define  PWR_CSR_WUF                         ((u16)0x0001)     /* Wakeup Flag */
01236 #define  PWR_CSR_SBF                         ((u16)0x0002)     /* Standby Flag */
01237 #define  PWR_CSR_PVDO                        ((u16)0x0004)     /* PVD Output */
01238 #define  PWR_CSR_EWUP                        ((u16)0x0100)     /* Enable WKUP pin */
01239

02267 /*****************  Bit definition for SysTick_CTRL register  *****************/
02268 #define  SysTick_CTRL_ENABLE                 ((u32)0x00000001)        /* Counter enable */
02269 #define  SysTick_CTRL_TICKINT                ((u32)0x00000002)        /* Counting down to 0 pends the SysTick handler */
02270 #define  SysTick_CTRL_CLKSOURCE              ((u32)0x00000004)        /* Clock source */
02271 #define  SysTick_CTRL_COUNTFLAG              ((u32)0x00010000)        /* Count Flag */
02272 
02273 
02274 /*****************  Bit definition for SysTick_LOAD register  *****************/
02275 #define  SysTick_LOAD_RELOAD                 ((u32)0x00FFFFFF)        /* Value to load into the SysTick Current Value Register when the counter reaches 0 */
02276 
02277 
02278 /*****************  Bit definition for SysTick_VAL register  ******************/
02279 #define  SysTick_VAL_CURRENT                 ((u32)0x00FFFFFF)        /* Current value at the time the register is accessed */
02280 
02281 
02282 /*****************  Bit definition for SysTick_CALIB register  ****************/
02283 #define  SysTick_CALIB_TENMS                 ((u32)0x00FFFFFF)        /* Reload value to use for 10ms timing */
02284 #define  SysTick_CALIB_SKEW                  ((u32)0x40000000)        /* Calibration value is not exactly 10 ms */
02285 #define  SysTick_CALIB_NOREF                 ((u32)0x80000000)        /* The reference clock is not provided */

02816 /*******************  Bit definition for DMA_ISR register  ********************/
02817 #define  DMA_ISR_GIF1                        ((u32)0x00000001)        /* Channel 1 Global interrupt flag */
02818 #define  DMA_ISR_TCIF1                       ((u32)0x00000002)        /* Channel 1 Transfer Complete flag */
02819 #define  DMA_ISR_HTIF1                       ((u32)0x00000004)        /* Channel 1 Half Transfer flag */
02820 #define  DMA_ISR_TEIF1                       ((u32)0x00000008)        /* Channel 1 Transfer Error flag */
02821 #define  DMA_ISR_GIF2                        ((u32)0x00000010)        /* Channel 2 Global interrupt flag */
02822 #define  DMA_ISR_TCIF2                       ((u32)0x00000020)        /* Channel 2 Transfer Complete flag */
02823 #define  DMA_ISR_HTIF2                       ((u32)0x00000040)        /* Channel 2 Half Transfer flag */
02824 #define  DMA_ISR_TEIF2                       ((u32)0x00000080)        /* Channel 2 Transfer Error flag */
02825 #define  DMA_ISR_GIF3                        ((u32)0x00000100)        /* Channel 3 Global interrupt flag */
02826 #define  DMA_ISR_TCIF3                       ((u32)0x00000200)        /* Channel 3 Transfer Complete flag */
02827 #define  DMA_ISR_HTIF3                       ((u32)0x00000400)        /* Channel 3 Half Transfer flag */
02828 #define  DMA_ISR_TEIF3                       ((u32)0x00000800)        /* Channel 3 Transfer Error flag */
02829 #define  DMA_ISR_GIF4                        ((u32)0x00001000)        /* Channel 4 Global interrupt flag */
02830 #define  DMA_ISR_TCIF4                       ((u32)0x00002000)        /* Channel 4 Transfer Complete flag */
02831 #define  DMA_ISR_HTIF4                       ((u32)0x00004000)        /* Channel 4 Half Transfer flag */
02832 #define  DMA_ISR_TEIF4                       ((u32)0x00008000)        /* Channel 4 Transfer Error flag */
02833 #define  DMA_ISR_GIF5                        ((u32)0x00010000)        /* Channel 5 Global interrupt flag */
02834 #define  DMA_ISR_TCIF5                       ((u32)0x00020000)        /* Channel 5 Transfer Complete flag */
02835 #define  DMA_ISR_HTIF5                       ((u32)0x00040000)        /* Channel 5 Half Transfer flag */
02836 #define  DMA_ISR_TEIF5                       ((u32)0x00080000)        /* Channel 5 Transfer Error flag */
02837 #define  DMA_ISR_GIF6                        ((u32)0x00100000)        /* Channel 6 Global interrupt flag */
02838 #define  DMA_ISR_TCIF6                       ((u32)0x00200000)        /* Channel 6 Transfer Complete flag */
02839 #define  DMA_ISR_HTIF6                       ((u32)0x00400000)        /* Channel 6 Half Transfer flag */
02840 #define  DMA_ISR_TEIF6                       ((u32)0x00800000)        /* Channel 6 Transfer Error flag */
02841 #define  DMA_ISR_GIF7                        ((u32)0x01000000)        /* Channel 7 Global interrupt flag */
02842 #define  DMA_ISR_TCIF7                       ((u32)0x02000000)        /* Channel 7 Transfer Complete flag */
02843 #define  DMA_ISR_HTIF7                       ((u32)0x04000000)        /* Channel 7 Half Transfer flag */
02844 #define  DMA_ISR_TEIF7                       ((u32)0x08000000)        /* Channel 7 Transfer Error flag */

02878 /*******************  Bit definition for DMA_CCR1 register  *******************/
02879 #define  DMA_CCR1_EN                         ((u16)0x0001)            /* Channel enable*/
02880 #define  DMA_CCR1_TCIE                       ((u16)0x0002)            /* Transfer complete interrupt enable */
02881 #define  DMA_CCR1_HTIE                       ((u16)0x0004)            /* Half Transfer interrupt enable */
02882 #define  DMA_CCR1_TEIE                       ((u16)0x0008)            /* Transfer error interrupt enable */
02883 #define  DMA_CCR1_DIR                        ((u16)0x0010)            /* Data transfer direction */
02884 #define  DMA_CCR1_CIRC                       ((u16)0x0020)            /* Circular mode */
02885 #define  DMA_CCR1_PINC                       ((u16)0x0040)            /* Peripheral increment mode */
02886 #define  DMA_CCR1_MINC                       ((u16)0x0080)            /* Memory increment mode */
02887 
02888 #define  DMA_CCR1_PSIZE                      ((u16)0x0300)            /* PSIZE[1:0] bits (Peripheral size) */
02889 #define  DMA_CCR1_PSIZE_0                    ((u16)0x0100)            /* Bit 0 */
02890 #define  DMA_CCR1_PSIZE_1                    ((u16)0x0200)            /* Bit 1 */
02891

02893 #define  DMA_CCR1_MSIZE_0                    ((u16)0x0400)            /* Bit 0 */
02894 #define  DMA_CCR1_MSIZE_1                    ((u16)0x0800)            /* Bit 1 */

03143 
03144 /********************  Bit definition for ADC_SR register  ********************/
03145 #define  ADC_SR_AWD                          ((u8)0x01)               /* Analog watchdog flag */
03146 #define  ADC_SR_EOC                          ((u8)0x02)               /* End of conversion */
03147 #define  ADC_SR_JEOC                         ((u8)0x04)               /* Injected channel end of conversion */
03148 #define  ADC_SR_JSTRT                        ((u8)0x08)               /* Injected channel Start flag */
03149 #define  ADC_SR_STRT                         ((u8)0x10)               /* Regular channel Start flag */
03150 
03151 
03152 /*******************  Bit definition for ADC_CR1 register  ********************/
03153 #define  ADC_CR1_AWDCH                       ((u32)0x0000001F)        /* AWDCH[4:0] bits (Analog watchdog channel select bits) */
03154 #define  ADC_CR1_AWDCH_0                     ((u32)0x00000001)        /* Bit 0 */
03155 #define  ADC_CR1_AWDCH_1                     ((u32)0x00000002)        /* Bit 1 */
03156 #define  ADC_CR1_AWDCH_2                     ((u32)0x00000004)        /* Bit 2 */
03157 #define  ADC_CR1_AWDCH_3                     ((u32)0x00000008)        /* Bit 3 */
03158 #define  ADC_CR1_AWDCH_4                     ((u32)0x00000010)        /* Bit 4 */
03159 
03160 #define  ADC_CR1_EOCIE                       ((u32)0x00000020)        /* Interrupt enable for EOC */
03161 #define  ADC_CR1_AWDIE                       ((u32)0x00000040)        /* AAnalog Watchdog interrupt enable */
03162 #define  ADC_CR1_JEOCIE                      ((u32)0x00000080)        /* Interrupt enable for injected channels */

04975 #define  SDIO_DLEN_DATALENGTH                ((u32)0x01FFFFFF)        /* Data length value */
04976 
04977 
04978 /******************  Bit definition for SDIO_DCTRL register  ******************/
04979 #define  SDIO_DCTRL_DTEN                     ((u16)0x0001)            /* Data transfer enabled bit */
04980 #define  SDIO_DCTRL_DTDIR                    ((u16)0x0002)            /* Data transfer direction selection */
04981 #define  SDIO_DCTRL_DTMODE                   ((u16)0x0004)            /* Data transfer mode selection */
04982 #define  SDIO_DCTRL_DMAEN                    ((u16)0x0008)            /* DMA enabled bit */
04983 
04984 #define  SDIO_DCTRL_DBLOCKSIZE               ((u16)0x00F0)            /* DBLOCKSIZE[3:0] bits (Data block size) */
04985 #define  SDIO_DCTRL_DBLOCKSIZE_0             ((u16)0x0010)            /* Bit 0 */
04986 #define  SDIO_DCTRL_DBLOCKSIZE_1             ((u16)0x0020)            /* Bit 1 */
04987 #define  SDIO_DCTRL_DBLOCKSIZE_2             ((u16)0x0040)            /* Bit 2 */
04988 #define  SDIO_DCTRL_DBLOCKSIZE_3             ((u16)0x0080)            /* Bit 3 */
04989 
04990 #define  SDIO_DCTRL_RWSTART                  ((u16)0x0100)            /* Read wait start */
04991 #define  SDIO_DCTRL_RWSTOP                   ((u16)0x0200)            /* Read wait stop */
04992 #define  SDIO_DCTRL_RWMOD                    ((u16)0x0400)            /* Read wait mode */
04993 #define  SDIO_DCTRL_SDIOEN                   ((u16)0x0800)            /* SD I/O enable functions */
04994 
04995 
04996 /******************  Bit definition for SDIO_DCOUNT register  *****************/
04997 #define  SDIO_DCOUNT_DATACOUNT               ((u32)0x01FFFFFF)        /* Data count value */
04998 
04999 
05000 /******************  Bit definition for SDIO_STA register  ********************/
05001 #define  SDIO_STA_CCRCFAIL                   ((u32)0x00000001)        /* Command response received (CRC check failed) */
05002 #define  SDIO_STA_DCRCFAIL                   ((u32)0x00000002)        /* Data block sent/received (CRC check failed) */
05003 #define  SDIO_STA_CTIMEOUT                   ((u32)0x00000004)        /* Command response timeout */
05004 #define  SDIO_STA_DTIMEOUT                   ((u32)0x00000008)        /* Data timeout */
05005 #define  SDIO_STA_TXUNDERR                   ((u32)0x00000010)        /* Transmit FIFO underrun error */
05006 #define  SDIO_STA_RXOVERR                    ((u32)0x00000020)        /* Received FIFO overrun error */
05007 #define  SDIO_STA_CMDREND                    ((u32)0x00000040)        /* Command response received (CRC check passed) */
05008 #define  SDIO_STA_CMDSENT                    ((u32)0x00000080)        /* Command sent (no response required) */
05009 #define  SDIO_STA_DATAEND                    ((u32)0x00000100)        /* Data end (data counter, SDIDCOUNT, is zero) */
05010 #define  SDIO_STA_STBITERR                   ((u32)0x00000200)        /* Start bit not detected on all data signals in wide bus mode */
05011 #define  SDIO_STA_DBCKEND                    ((u32)0x00000400)        /* Data block sent/received (CRC check passed) */
05012 #define  SDIO_STA_CMDACT                     ((u32)0x00000800)        /* Command transfer in progress */
05013 #define  SDIO_STA_TXACT                      ((u32)0x00001000)        /* Data transmit in progress */
05014 #define  SDIO_STA_RXACT                      ((u32)0x00002000)        /* Data receive in progress */
05015 #define  SDIO_STA_TXFIFOHE                   ((u32)0x00004000)        /* Transmit FIFO Half Empty: at least 8 words can be written into the FIFO */
05016 #define  SDIO_STA_RXFIFOHF                   ((u32)0x00008000)        /* Receive FIFO Half Full: there are at least 8 words in the FIFO */
05017 #define  SDIO_STA_TXFIFOF                    ((u32)0x00010000)        /* Transmit FIFO full */
05018 #define  SDIO_STA_RXFIFOF                    ((u32)0x00020000)        /* Receive FIFO full */
05019 #define  SDIO_STA_TXFIFOE                    ((u32)0x00040000)        /* Transmit FIFO empty */
05020 #define  SDIO_STA_RXFIFOE                    ((u32)0x00080000)        /* Receive FIFO empty */
05021 #define  SDIO_STA_TXDAVL                     ((u32)0x00100000)        /* Data available in transmit FIFO */
05022 #define  SDIO_STA_RXDAVL                     ((u32)0x00200000)        /* Data available in receive FIFO */
05023 #define  SDIO_STA_SDIOIT                     ((u32)0x00400000)        /* SDIO interrupt received */
05024 #define  SDIO_STA_CEATAEND                   ((u32)0x00800000)        /* CE-ATA command completion signal received for CMD61 */
05025 
05026 
05027 /*******************  Bit definition for SDIO_ICR register  *******************/
05028 #define  SDIO_ICR_CCRCFAILC                  ((u32)0x00000001)        /* CCRCFAIL flag clear bit */
05029 #define  SDIO_ICR_DCRCFAILC                  ((u32)0x00000002)        /* DCRCFAIL flag clear bit */
05030 #define  SDIO_ICR_CTIMEOUTC                  ((u32)0x00000004)        /* CTIMEOUT flag clear bit */
05031 #define  SDIO_ICR_DTIMEOUTC                  ((u32)0x00000008)        /* DTIMEOUT flag clear bit */
05032 #define  SDIO_ICR_TXUNDERRC                  ((u32)0x00000010)        /* TXUNDERR flag clear bit */
05033 #define  SDIO_ICR_RXOVERRC                   ((u32)0x00000020)        /* RXOVERR flag clear bit */
05034 #define  SDIO_ICR_CMDRENDC                   ((u32)0x00000040)        /* CMDREND flag clear bit */
05035 #define  SDIO_ICR_CMDSENTC                   ((u32)0x00000080)        /* CMDSENT flag clear bit */
05036 #define  SDIO_ICR_DATAENDC                   ((u32)0x00000100)        /* DATAEND flag clear bit */
05037 #define  SDIO_ICR_STBITERRC                  ((u32)0x00000200)        /* STBITERR flag clear bit */
05038 #define  SDIO_ICR_DBCKENDC                   ((u32)0x00000400)        /* DBCKEND flag clear bit */
05039 #define  SDIO_ICR_SDIOITC                    ((u32)0x00400000)        /* SDIOIT flag clear bit */
05040 #define  SDIO_ICR_CEATAENDC                  ((u32)0x00800000)        /* CEATAEND flag clear bit */
05041 
05042 
05043 /******************  Bit definition for SDIO_MASK register  *******************/
05044 #define  SDIO_MASK_CCRCFAILIE                ((u32)0x00000001)        /* Command CRC Fail Interrupt Enable */
05045 #define  SDIO_MASK_DCRCFAILIE                ((u32)0x00000002)        /* Data CRC Fail Interrupt Enable */
05046 #define  SDIO_MASK_CTIMEOUTIE                ((u32)0x00000004)        /* Command TimeOut Interrupt Enable */
05047 #define  SDIO_MASK_DTIMEOUTIE                ((u32)0x00000008)        /* Data TimeOut Interrupt Enable */
05048 #define  SDIO_MASK_TXUNDERRIE                ((u32)0x00000010)        /* Tx FIFO UnderRun Error Interrupt Enable */
05049 #define  SDIO_MASK_RXOVERRIE                 ((u32)0x00000020)        /* Rx FIFO OverRun Error Interrupt Enable */
05050 #define  SDIO_MASK_CMDRENDIE                 ((u32)0x00000040)        /* Command Response Received Interrupt Enable */
05051 #define  SDIO_MASK_CMDSENTIE                 ((u32)0x00000080)        /* Command Sent Interrupt Enable */
05052 #define  SDIO_MASK_DATAENDIE                 ((u32)0x00000100)        /* Data End Interrupt Enable */
05053 #define  SDIO_MASK_STBITERRIE                ((u32)0x00000200)        /* Start Bit Error Interrupt Enable */
05054 #define  SDIO_MASK_DBCKENDIE                 ((u32)0x00000400)        /* Data Block End Interrupt Enable */
05055 #define  SDIO_MASK_CMDACTIE                  ((u32)0x00000800)        /* CCommand Acting Interrupt Enable */
05056 #define  SDIO_MASK_TXACTIE                   ((u32)0x00001000)        /* Data Transmit Acting Interrupt Enable */
05057 #define  SDIO_MASK_RXACTIE                   ((u32)0x00002000)        /* Data receive acting interrupt enabled */
05058 #define  SDIO_MASK_TXFIFOHEIE                ((u32)0x00004000)        /* Tx FIFO Half Empty interrupt Enable */
05059 #define  SDIO_MASK_RXFIFOHFIE                ((u32)0x00008000)        /* Rx FIFO Half Full interrupt Enable */
05060 #define  SDIO_MASK_TXFIFOFIE                 ((u32)0x00010000)        /* Tx FIFO Full interrupt Enable */
05061 #define  SDIO_MASK_RXFIFOFIE                 ((u32)0x00020000)        /* Rx FIFO Full interrupt Enable */
05062 #define  SDIO_MASK_TXFIFOEIE                 ((u32)0x00040000)        /* Tx FIFO Empty interrupt Enable */
05063 #define  SDIO_MASK_RXFIFOEIE                 ((u32)0x00080000)        /* Rx FIFO Empty interrupt Enable */
05064 #define  SDIO_MASK_TXDAVLIE                  ((u32)0x00100000)        /* Data available in Tx FIFO interrupt Enable */
05065 #define  SDIO_MASK_RXDAVLIE                  ((u32)0x00200000)        /* Data available in Rx FIFO interrupt Enable */
05066 #define  SDIO_MASK_SDIOITIE                  ((u32)0x00400000)        /* SDIO Mode Interrupt Received interrupt Enable */
05067 #define  SDIO_MASK_CEATAENDIE                ((u32)0x00800000)        /* CE-ATA command completion signal received Interrupt Enable */
05068

05286 /* Common registers */
05287 /*******************  Bit definition for USB_CNTR register  *******************/
05288 #define  USB_CNTR_FRES                       ((u16)0x0001)            /* Force USB Reset */
05289 #define  USB_CNTR_PDWN                       ((u16)0x0002)            /* Power down */
05290 #define  USB_CNTR_LP_MODE                    ((u16)0x0004)            /* Low-power mode */
05291 #define  USB_CNTR_FSUSP                      ((u16)0x0008)            /* Force suspend */
05292 #define  USB_CNTR_RESUME                     ((u16)0x0010)            /* Resume request */
05293 #define  USB_CNTR_ESOFM                      ((u16)0x0100)            /* Expected Start Of Frame Interrupt Mask */
05294 #define  USB_CNTR_SOFM                       ((u16)0x0200)            /* Start Of Frame Interrupt Mask */
05295 #define  USB_CNTR_RESETM                     ((u16)0x0400)            /* RESET Interrupt Mask */
05296 #define  USB_CNTR_SUSPM                      ((u16)0x0800)            /* Suspend mode Interrupt Mask */
05297 #define  USB_CNTR_WKUPM                      ((u16)0x1000)            /* Wakeup Interrupt Mask */
05298 #define  USB_CNTR_ERRM                       ((u16)0x2000)            /* Error Interrupt Mask */
05299 #define  USB_CNTR_PMAOVRM                    ((u16)0x4000)            /* Packet Memory Area Over / Underrun Interrupt Mask */
05300 #define  USB_CNTR_CTRM                       ((u16)0x8000)            /* Correct Transfer Interrupt Mask */
05301

05307 #define  USB_ISTR_SOF                        ((u16)0x0200)            /* Start Of Frame */
05308 #define  USB_ISTR_RESET                      ((u16)0x0400)            /* USB RESET request */
05309 #define  USB_ISTR_SUSP                       ((u16)0x0800)            /* Suspend mode request */

05313 #define  USB_ISTR_CTR                        ((u16)0x8000)            /* Correct Transfer */

05832 /* CAN control and status registers */
05833 /*******************  Bit definition for CAN_MCR register  ********************/
05834 #define  CAN_MCR_INRQ                        ((u16)0x0001)            /* Initialization Request */
05835 #define  CAN_MCR_SLEEP                       ((u16)0x0002)            /* Sleep Mode Request */
05836 #define  CAN_MCR_TXFP                        ((u16)0x0004)            /* Transmit FIFO Priority */
05837 #define  CAN_MCR_RFLM                        ((u16)0x0008)            /* Receive FIFO Locked Mode */
05838 #define  CAN_MCR_NART                        ((u16)0x0010)            /* No Automatic Retransmission */
05839 #define  CAN_MCR_AWUM                        ((u16)0x0020)            /* Automatic Wakeup Mode */
05840 #define  CAN_MCR_ABOM                        ((u16)0x0040)            /* Automatic Bus-Off Management */
05841 #define  CAN_MCR_TTCM                        ((u16)0x0080)            /* Time Triggered Communication Mode */
05842 #define  CAN_MCR_RESET                       ((u16)0x8000)            /* bxCAN software master reset */
05843 
05844 
05845 /*******************  Bit definition for CAN_MSR register  ********************/
05846 #define  CAN_MSR_INAK                        ((u16)0x0001)            /* Initialization Acknowledge */
05847 #define  CAN_MSR_SLAK                        ((u16)0x0002)            /* Sleep Acknowledge */
05848 #define  CAN_MSR_ERRI                        ((u16)0x0004)            /* Error Interrupt */
05849 #define  CAN_MSR_WKUI                        ((u16)0x0008)            /* Wakeup Interrupt */
05850 #define  CAN_MSR_SLAKI                       ((u16)0x0010)            /* Sleep Acknowledge Interrupt */
05851 #define  CAN_MSR_TXM                         ((u16)0x0100)            /* Transmit Mode */
05852 #define  CAN_MSR_RXM                         ((u16)0x0200)            /* Receive Mode */
05853 #define  CAN_MSR_SAMP                        ((u16)0x0400)            /* Last Sample Point */
05854 #define  CAN_MSR_RX                          ((u16)0x0800)            /* CAN Rx Signal */
05855 
05856 
05857 /*******************  Bit definition for CAN_TSR register  ********************/
05858 #define  CAN_TSR_RQCP0                       ((u32)0x00000001)        /* Request Completed Mailbox0 */
05859 #define  CAN_TSR_TXOK0                       ((u32)0x00000002)        /* Transmission OK of Mailbox0 */
05860 #define  CAN_TSR_ALST0                       ((u32)0x00000004)        /* Arbitration Lost for Mailbox0 */
05861 #define  CAN_TSR_TERR0                       ((u32)0x00000008)        /* Transmission Error of Mailbox0 */
05862 #define  CAN_TSR_ABRQ0                       ((u32)0x00000080)        /* Abort Request for Mailbox0 */
05863 #define  CAN_TSR_RQCP1                       ((u32)0x00000100)        /* Request Completed Mailbox1 */
05864 #define  CAN_TSR_TXOK1                       ((u32)0x00000200)        /* Transmission OK of Mailbox1 */
05865 #define  CAN_TSR_ALST1                       ((u32)0x00000400)        /* Arbitration Lost for Mailbox1 */
05866 #define  CAN_TSR_TERR1                       ((u32)0x00000800)        /* Transmission Error of Mailbox1 */
05867 #define  CAN_TSR_ABRQ1                       ((u32)0x00008000)        /* Abort Request for Mailbox 1 */
05868 #define  CAN_TSR_RQCP2                       ((u32)0x00010000)        /* Request Completed Mailbox2 */
05869 #define  CAN_TSR_TXOK2                       ((u32)0x00020000)        /* Transmission OK of Mailbox 2 */
05870 #define  CAN_TSR_ALST2                       ((u32)0x00040000)        /* Arbitration Lost for mailbox 2 */
05871 #define  CAN_TSR_TERR2                       ((u32)0x00080000)        /* Transmission Error of Mailbox 2 */
05872 #define  CAN_TSR_ABRQ2                       ((u32)0x00800000)        /* Abort Request for Mailbox 2 */
05873 #define  CAN_TSR_CODE                        ((u32)0x03000000)        /* Mailbox Code */
05874 
05875 #define  CAN_TSR_TME                         ((u32)0x1C000000)        /* TME[2:0] bits */
05876 #define  CAN_TSR_TME0                        ((u32)0x04000000)        /* Transmit Mailbox 0 Empty */
05877 #define  CAN_TSR_TME1                        ((u32)0x08000000)        /* Transmit Mailbox 1 Empty */
05878 #define  CAN_TSR_TME2                        ((u32)0x10000000)        /* Transmit Mailbox 2 Empty */
05879 
05880 #define  CAN_TSR_LOW                         ((u32)0xE0000000)        /* LOW[2:0] bits */
05881 #define  CAN_TSR_LOW0                        ((u32)0x20000000)        /* Lowest Priority Flag for Mailbox 0 */
05882 #define  CAN_TSR_LOW1                        ((u32)0x40000000)        /* Lowest Priority Flag for Mailbox 1 */
05883 #define  CAN_TSR_LOW2                        ((u32)0x80000000)        /* Lowest Priority Flag for Mailbox 2 */
05884

07586 /* Exported macro ------------------------------------------------------------*/
07587 #define SET_BIT(REG, BIT)     ((REG) |= (BIT))
07588 
07589 #define CLEAR_BIT(REG, BIT)   ((REG) &= ~(BIT))
07590 
07591 #define READ_BIT(REG, BIT)    ((REG) & (BIT))
07592 
07593 #define CLEAR_REG(REG)        ((REG) = 0x0)
07594 
07595 #define WRITE_REG(REG, VAL)   ((REG) = VAL)
07596 
07597 #define READ_REG(REG)         ((REG))
07598 
07599 #define MODIFY_REG(REG, CLEARMASK, SETMASK)  WRITE_REG((REG), (((READ_REG(REG)) & (~CLEARMASK)) | (SETMASK)))
